Some gun-wielding arsonists have reportedly attacked the residence of a former Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) lawmaker, Nnenna Ukeje. Ukeje represented Bende Federal Constituency in the House of Representatives. The incident happened at her Alayi country home in Bende council.   Govt kicks off process for Kyari’s extradition to U.S.     ‘Police illegally arrest, detain our men’     Ex-banker jailed 10 years for theft   Information about the incident was sketchy at press time, but our correspondent learnt that the arsonists entered the compound after scaling the fence. The Nation was told that the arsonists set ablaze two Sports Utility Vehicles (SUVs) parked in the compound. They also burnt the ex-lawmaker’s air conditioner units and parts of the building.. The police command was yet to respond to the incident, but a reliable source told The Nation that the Army, Department of State Services (DSS), the police and chairman of Bende council, Emmanuel Onwuchekwa, have visited the scene.